Diabetes is a serious condition where your blood glucose level is too high.
There are two main types, Type 1 and Type 2. They're different conditions, but
Type 1 diabetes is a serious condition where your blood glucose level is too
high. About 10% of people with diabetes have Type 1.
Type 2 diabetes is a serious condition where your blood glucose level is too
high. About 90% of people with diabetes have Type 2.
